.TH "RTCTRANSPORTSTATS.TLSVERSION" "3JS" "June 24, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCTransportStats.tlsVersion \- RTCTransportStats: tlsVersion property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]tlsVersion\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCTransportStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the negotiated TLS
version of an underlying DTLS transport.
.PP
It is only present for DTLS transports, and only exists after DTLS has
been negotiated.
.PP
The value comes from the DTLS handshake \f[CR]ServerHello.version\f[R],
and is represented as four upper case hexadecimal digits, where the
digits represent the two bytes of the version.
Note however that the bytes might not map directly to version numbers.
For example, DTLS represents version 1.2 as \f[CR]\(aqFEFD\(aq\f[R]
which numerically is \f[CR]{254, 253}\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A string that indicates the negotiated DTS transport.
